  "architecture_summary": "Vision Transformer (ViT) splits an image into fixed-size patches, linearly embeds the patches, adds position embeddings and a learnable [class] token, and feeds the resulting sequence to a standard Transformer encoder for classification. The paper also studies a hybrid variant that uses CNN feature maps as input, plus fine-tuning at higher resolution and a preliminary masked patch prediction self-supervision setup.",
